Chrome Guard

Chrome Guard is a lightweight desktop tool that launches Google Chrome with a dedicated low-latency profile and monitors how the browser uses system resources. It provides a simple Tkinter interface that shows real-time Chrome CPU activity, identifies heavy processes (tab renderers, extensions, GPU coordination process, utilities), and highlights potential performance spikes.

Features

Launch Chrome with optimized flags for lower latency

Monitor total Chrome CPU usage

Identify the highest-CPU Chrome process

Display estimated per-tab CPU contribution using the Chrome DevTools Protocol

Show real-time usage meters in the UI

Generate alerts when Chrome processes exhibit sustained high load

Simple desktop UI to launch and observe Chrome

